<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-04-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-04-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8585: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-06T03:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                                        1927—3 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 5—3:45
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>354. Following from Patrol commander: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“0304. <hi rend="italic">Polos</hi> evacuating Changsha as soon
                                    as possible. Labor agitation developing over night makes this
                                    imperative. Consul estimates will be ready leave April 7.
                                    1329.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>